observationText: The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line was derived from a metastatic melanoma lesion and harbors a BRAF V600E mutation.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line exhibited sensitivity to the BRAF inhibitor vemurafenib in vitro.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line formed tumors when injected subcutaneously into immunodeficient mice.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line exhibited a mesenchymal-like phenotype with elongated cell morphology.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line showed increased expression of the melanoma stem cell markers CD271 and CD166 compared to other melanoma cell lines.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line exhibited increased invasiveness and migratory capacity compared to other melanoma cell lines in in vitro assays.
The MUG-Mel1 clone C8 cell line showed increased expression of the transcription factor ZEB1, which is associated with epithelial-mesenchymal transition and invasiveness.
